<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224053>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dichotomius eucranioides (A) black arrow indicating crenulated clypeal margin; D. sexdentatus (B) black arrow indicating tooth or protuberance on clypeogenal junction (this is also seen on D. eucranioides); D. nisus (C) black arrow indicating the asymmetry of the parameres; D. crinicollis (D) black arrows indicating pilosity on the hypomeron; D. superbus (E) white arrow indicating gibbosities on the pronotum; D. schiffleri (D. sericeus species group) (F) white arrow indicating a fovea on the posterior angle of the pronotum; D. speciosus (G) black arrows indicating cephalic transversal carina; D. agenor (H) black arrow indicating male cephalic carina; D. glaucus (D. carbornarius species group) (I) elytra microsculpture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224053/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224052>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dichotomius mysticus (A) dorsal habitus; (B) dorsal view of genitalia; (C) hind wing; and (D) tarsi and tarsal claw (indicated by black arrow). Dichotomius vidaurrei (E) dorsal habitus; (F) dorsal view of genitalia; and (G) hind wing. Scale bar = 1.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224052/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

